headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson sank five 3-pointers while scoring 23 points and the Utah Jazz protected the NBA’s best record with a runaway 112-91 win over the Atlanta Hawks on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson's 23 points power Jazz past slumping Hawks, 112-91

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Kelly Oubre Jr. scored a career-high 40 points, Stephen Curry had 28 and the Golden State Warriors went small in a runaway win, beating the Dallas Mavericks 147-116 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banged-up Warriors go small, overpower Mavericks 147-116

headlines.description: — Gary Trent Jr. scored 24 points and Enes Kanter had 17 points and 18 rebounds to lead the undermanned Portland Trail Blazers to a 121-105 win over the Philadelphia 76ers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trent, Anthony lead undermanned Portland past 76ers 121-105

headlines.description: — John Wall scored 22 points, Eric Gordon added 20 and the Houston Rockets beat the Memphis Grizzlies 115-103 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wall, Gordon lead Rockets past Grizzlies 115-103

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 27 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists, Dennis Schröder added 21 points and the Los Angeles Lakers roared away in the second half for a 114-93 victory over the Denver Nuggets on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron's triple-double powers Lakers past Nuggets, 114-93
